"signal_description": "The SIGNAL query is designed to extract data from the table named 'defaultview-545'. It selects the quarter of the last 'END_TIME' value, the average difference between the last and first 'end_time' values, and the 'PO Business Unit' column. The query only includes records where the last 'END_TIME' value (truncated to the day) is on or after January 1, 2022, and the first 'END_TIME' value (also truncated to the day) is on or before June 30, 2022. Additionally, it only includes records where the 'PO Item Line Type' is not null. The results are ordered by the 'PO Business Unit' and the quarter, in ascending order, with any null values appearing first. The query fills in any missing quarters in the time series with null values and groups the results. The query is limited to the first 500 records."
